==English==

===Etymology===
Spanish ''cedilla'' < older ''[[zedilla]]'' (“little [[zed]]”, “little z”).

===Noun===
# {{orthography}}: A mark placed under the letter ''c'' in Catalan, French and Portuguese to indicate that it is pronounced before ''a'', ''o'', or ''u'' as it would be before ''e'' or ''i'': ''menaçant'', ''almoço''. See [[ç|Ç]].

